Evaluation of the Content Information and Utility of the Different Modules of VloV
Across the functions (Table 2), the percentage of responses distributed in higher levels of appropriateness were: mood scale record, money earned display, sobriety calculator, and treatment skills review. While meditation tracks, “red button”—utility and content—obtained lower scores. Profile content and daily consumption records were scored mostly neutral.


